WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.360
Chen Hao Wei, can you help me with mathematics?
[Episode 3]

00:00:02.360 --> 00:00:03.961
Sure.
[Love Confession from the Shooting Stars]

00:00:04.637 --> 00:00:06.706
Why is your exam paper swimming with turtles?

00:00:06.706 --> 00:00:09.509
Drawing turtles make me really happy.

00:00:09.509 --> 00:00:11.444
Didn't know turtles could do that.

00:00:11.444 --> 00:00:12.445
How about you teach me how to draw?

00:00:12.445 --> 00:00:15.548
Sure, I'll teach you
the easiest drawing method.

00:00:15.548 --> 00:00:19.152
Start with a huge oval.

00:00:19.152 --> 00:00:21.687
Add tons of circles inside.

00:00:23.356 --> 00:00:25.159
Give it boomerang limbs.

00:00:25.159 --> 00:00:27.592
- Boomerang?
- Yep.

00:00:28.628 --> 00:00:31.961
Now, you have to draw a huge head.

00:00:33.066 --> 00:00:34.601
Finish with a tiny tail.

00:00:34.601 --> 00:00:37.803
- Easy, right?
- Huge head, tiny tail.

00:00:38.538 --> 00:00:40.106
So cute. Thanks.

00:00:40.106 --> 00:00:41.941
I've mastered it.

00:00:42.742 --> 00:00:44.344
I'm really curious about something.

00:00:44.344 --> 00:00:47.246
- What is it?
- Why do you keep smiling?

00:00:47.881 --> 00:00:49.049
- Do I?
- Look at yourself.

00:00:49.049 --> 00:00:51.651
Aren't you smiling now?

00:00:51.651 --> 00:00:53.386
What's wrong with smiling?

00:00:53.386 --> 00:00:56.322
But don't you ever feel upset?

00:00:56.322 --> 00:00:58.059
Or maybe sad?

00:01:01.795 --> 00:01:02.996
I...

00:01:02.996 --> 00:01:05.398
I've got no clue.

00:01:05.398 --> 00:01:08.501
How about I teach you a new method?

00:01:08.501 --> 00:01:10.603
What is it?

00:01:10.603 --> 00:01:14.441
Silently recite 1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:01:14.441 --> 00:01:16.876
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7?

00:01:16.876 --> 00:01:20.313
Don't you feel at peace?

00:01:20.313 --> 00:01:21.948
Why these numbers?

00:01:21.948 --> 00:01:25.985
Because they're the most mysterious
numbers in the world.

00:01:25.985 --> 00:01:28.955
Some people call them God's chosen digits.

00:01:28.955 --> 00:01:31.791
Others say they're the code to the universe.

00:01:31.791 --> 00:01:36.062
But they're just a chain
of cyclic numbers in math.

00:01:36.062 --> 00:01:38.164
When they're multiplied up to six,

00:01:38.164 --> 00:01:41.766
the numbers don't change,
and their sequence doesn't change either.

00:01:41.768 --> 00:01:45.448
It's the same six digits.

00:02:53.373 --> 00:02:54.374
Aren't you a top student?

00:02:54.374 --> 00:02:56.476
Chen Hao Wei, pick up the damn phone.

00:02:56.476 --> 00:02:58.077
- Such a lame mistake.
- I just want to hear your explanation.

00:02:58.077 --> 00:02:59.679
What happened to the funds?

00:02:59.679 --> 00:03:01.447
So, you just used up Mr. Lin's money?

00:03:01.447 --> 00:03:03.583
- We tried our best, but...
- I know that investments have risks.

00:03:03.583 --> 00:03:05.118
But you made such grand promises.

00:03:05.118 --> 00:03:06.219
Now, what do we do?

00:03:06.219 --> 00:03:07.955
- What about everyone's hard work?
- I invested in bonds after your advice.

00:03:07.955 --> 00:03:08.955
The same with endowments.

00:03:08.955 --> 00:03:11.491
1, 4, 2, 5, 8, 7.

00:03:11.491 --> 00:03:13.327
- 1, 4, 2, 5, 8, 7.
- Now, I'm on shit terms with the bank.

00:03:13.327 --> 00:03:14.327
They refuse my loan requests.

00:03:14.327 --> 00:03:15.628
- 1, 4, 2, 5, 8, 7.
- I'm out of the trading game.

00:03:15.628 --> 00:03:16.763
What am I to do now?

00:03:16.763 --> 00:03:17.764
How about you speak with him?

00:03:17.764 --> 00:03:19.599
- 1, 4, 2, 5, 8, 7.
- Come on, help me.

00:03:19.599 --> 00:03:22.001
Chen Hao Wei!

00:03:22.001 --> 00:03:25.170
1, 4, 2, 5, 8, 7.

00:03:27.173 --> 00:03:29.656
1, 4, 2, 5, 8, 7.

00:03:41.254 --> 00:03:44.123
Excuse me, are you here to check in?

00:03:47.527 --> 00:03:48.872
Miss?

00:04:06.207 --> 00:04:08.681
Pick one card.

00:04:08.681 --> 00:04:10.015
Huh?

00:04:21.494 --> 00:04:23.164
I knew you'd need help finding your way.

00:04:23.164 --> 00:04:24.196
Is He Xiang Yong here?
I'm looking for him.

00:04:24.196 --> 00:04:25.781
-

00:04:27.300 --> 00:04:29.168
Bring the luggage in.

00:04:48.755 --> 00:04:52.997
So, you're the comic artist
working with Xiang Yong?

00:04:55.561 --> 00:04:56.829
Can I ask you a question?

00:04:56.829 --> 00:04:59.932
When Xiang Yong is in the office and at work...

00:04:59.932 --> 00:05:01.801
- Xi Xi!
- Are you... Don't yell!

00:05:01.801 --> 00:05:03.735
Are you trying to scare me into my grave?

00:05:04.470 --> 00:05:08.675
I'm just curious about
Xiang Yong's attitude at work.

00:05:08.675 --> 00:05:11.377
And how he's doing in the office.

00:05:11.377 --> 00:05:14.113
Wh-Why are you here?

00:05:16.382 --> 00:05:18.717
Strange, do you know her?

00:05:21.254 --> 00:05:23.222
Sir, you don't read comics.

00:05:23.222 --> 00:05:24.524
She's super famous.

00:05:24.524 --> 00:05:26.172
"Hunter's Gentle Vacation,"

00:05:26.172 --> 00:05:29.028
"Sweets, Seeds, Prophecy Diaries,"
"Goddess Zandeer" are all her works.

00:05:29.028 --> 00:05:30.763
I love her comics.

00:05:30.763 --> 00:05:33.132
You're my idol.

00:05:35.501 --> 00:05:37.436
But why are you here?

00:05:38.304 --> 00:05:40.373
- Are there any available rooms?
- What are you doing?

00:05:40.373 --> 00:05:41.808
She's clearly here as a guest.

00:05:41.808 --> 00:05:44.077
What? Is there a problem?

00:05:44.077 --> 00:05:45.111
Nah, sir.

00:05:45.111 --> 00:05:47.480
Your only available room hasn't been
tidied up after the last check-out.

00:05:47.480 --> 00:05:50.216
And I haven't scrubbed the toilet bowl.

00:05:50.216 --> 00:05:51.918
That room is also leaking water.

00:05:51.918 --> 00:05:54.253
I don't think anyone should live there.

00:05:54.253 --> 00:05:55.722
How many days do you plan on staying here?

00:05:55.722 --> 00:05:57.256
Three.

00:05:57.256 --> 00:05:59.659
Wait, that empty room
really has water leakage.

00:05:59.659 --> 00:06:00.660
- The floor is soaked.
- Hao Wei, help this lady check in.

00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:03.663
-

00:06:03.663 --> 00:06:05.531
- Sure.
- Zhong Xiao You!

00:06:07.600 --> 00:06:10.769
Bring her luggage to 201!

00:06:11.437 --> 00:06:14.306
201 has no water leakages,
I can guarantee that.

00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:17.054
Please check in here.

00:06:19.679 --> 00:06:22.315
Miss, this way, please. Sorry about the fuss.

00:06:22.315 --> 00:06:23.349
Du Du, come here.
Get in the shade.

00:06:23.349 --> 00:06:25.184
-

00:06:49.575 --> 00:06:51.526
Why sneak up here alone?

00:06:53.212 --> 00:06:54.747
To read.

00:06:54.747 --> 00:06:56.682
And admire the scenery.

00:06:59.252 --> 00:07:00.986
You're avoiding Xi Xi, huh?

00:07:02.622 --> 00:07:04.223
What?

00:07:06.793 --> 00:07:08.827
Why do you know Xi Xi?

00:07:11.197 --> 00:07:12.665
I've read her comics.
My friend's also her editor.

00:07:12.665 --> 00:07:14.367
-

00:07:14.367 --> 00:07:16.941
I don't need to divulge
all these to you, right?

00:07:19.639 --> 00:07:22.542
But when Mr. He was talking to her,
why did you look so jittery?

00:07:22.542 --> 00:07:24.610
-

00:07:27.146 --> 00:07:28.580
Did I?

00:07:29.882 --> 00:07:31.884
Are you scared of caterpillars?

00:07:31.884 --> 00:07:34.086
What caterpillars?

00:07:34.086 --> 00:07:35.555
I wasn't...

00:07:35.555 --> 00:07:37.322
I wasn't nervous.

00:07:39.859 --> 00:07:42.571
Are you hiding something
about He Xiang Yong?

00:07:44.030 --> 00:07:45.942
You've got a wild imagination.

00:07:55.808 --> 00:07:57.337
What are you doing?

00:08:00.713 --> 00:08:03.045
Did you date He Xiang Yong?

00:08:07.086 --> 00:08:08.587
Answer me!

00:08:11.357 --> 00:08:14.427
Yes, totally inseparable!

00:08:14.427 --> 00:08:16.412
Couldn't even spend a second apart.

00:08:19.866 --> 00:08:21.555
Inseparable?

00:08:25.771 --> 00:08:28.007
That's a relief.

00:08:28.007 --> 00:08:29.471
What? Why?

00:08:30.910 --> 00:08:33.992
That just means you've never dated him.

00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:36.974
Ridiculous.

00:08:38.918 --> 00:08:40.219
Wait.

00:08:40.219 --> 00:08:41.254
Didn't you say we should keep our distance
and not get in the other's way?

00:08:41.254 --> 00:08:42.622
-

00:08:42.622 --> 00:08:45.053
Why are you so concerned
about me now?

00:08:46.726 --> 00:08:48.528
Nah, it's nothing.

00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:50.696
Just some friendly concern.

00:08:51.664 --> 00:08:54.133
Huh, really?

00:08:54.133 --> 00:08:58.380
Your questions didn't sound
like friendly concern.

00:08:59.238 --> 00:09:01.582
It sounded like...

00:09:03.342 --> 00:09:04.770
Well?

00:09:06.979 --> 00:09:10.349
Like you were calling the kettle black!

00:09:10.349 --> 00:09:12.150
Got something on?

00:09:14.120 --> 00:09:15.154
It's nothing.
We're getting along wonderfully.

00:09:15.154 --> 00:09:16.856
-

00:09:16.856 --> 00:09:20.025
She wants to know if we have time.

00:09:21.627 --> 00:09:23.763
Are you planning on visiting somewhere?

00:09:23.763 --> 00:09:25.430
Breathe.

00:09:26.732 --> 00:09:28.367
Breathe?

00:09:29.068 --> 00:09:32.438
She probably wants to head out.

00:09:32.438 --> 00:09:34.106
Right?

00:09:35.441 --> 00:09:36.676
That's great.

00:09:36.676 --> 00:09:37.877
I can give you a ride.
Rent a bike yourself.

00:09:37.877 --> 00:09:38.978
-

00:09:38.978 --> 00:09:41.607
I'm sure girls want to ride their own bike.

00:09:50.489 --> 00:09:51.985
What are you staring at?

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:56.529
Why do you know her so well?

00:09:56.529 --> 00:09:59.007
Maybe I'm just more sincere with others.

00:10:02.902 --> 00:10:04.517
Sincere?

00:11:08.034 --> 00:11:11.237
I used to love gazing at the sea.

00:11:11.237 --> 00:11:12.638
- But that's as far as I go.
- I can't swim.

00:11:12.638 --> 00:11:15.741
-

00:11:15.741 --> 00:11:17.643
Whenever I hear sounds of the sea,
I imagine I'm floating on it.

00:11:17.643 --> 00:11:20.879
-

00:11:31.824 --> 00:11:33.047
Well?

00:11:36.028 --> 00:11:37.633
I'll take some photos for you.

00:11:44.370 --> 00:11:47.439
One, two, three.

00:11:57.850 --> 00:12:01.487
If you're feeling troubled,

00:12:01.487 --> 00:12:05.490
you can come here to relax and let loose.

00:12:06.392 --> 00:12:12.964
Face the sea and count 1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:12:25.745 --> 00:12:28.380
7... 7 by 7 is 49.

00:12:28.380 --> 00:12:29.248
8 by 8 is 64.
9 by 9 is 81.

00:12:29.248 --> 00:12:30.797
-

00:12:31.684 --> 00:12:34.120
You can sing, too.

00:12:34.120 --> 00:12:36.522
When you're done singing or counting,

00:12:36.522 --> 00:12:38.657
you'll realize that nothing really matters.

00:12:38.657 --> 00:12:40.459
All your troubles will vanish.

00:12:40.459 --> 00:12:41.627
I'm serious.

00:12:41.627 --> 00:12:43.381
It's just that magical.

00:12:51.871 --> 00:12:53.860
I'll take another photo for you.

00:13:05.985 --> 00:13:07.375
We're here.

00:13:11.457 --> 00:13:13.392
Li Wan Zhe.

00:13:13.392 --> 00:13:14.728
Three bowls of shaved ice.
Green bean milk shaved ice.

00:13:14.728 --> 00:13:15.794
-

00:13:15.794 --> 00:13:17.463
- And a shaved ice with jelly.
- Over here.

00:13:17.463 --> 00:13:21.033
Just get Xi Xi some shaved ice
with tricolored taro balls.

00:13:21.033 --> 00:13:22.034
Make sure to cook the taro balls fresh.
Move quickly.

00:13:22.034 --> 00:13:23.802
-

00:13:28.541 --> 00:13:30.009
Angela.

00:13:30.009 --> 00:13:32.077
Hao Wei! Done ordering?

00:13:32.077 --> 00:13:33.445
- Yep.
- Okay.

00:13:33.445 --> 00:13:36.047
Xiao You, guests are here.

00:13:39.485 --> 00:13:40.686
Xi Xi, hear me out.

00:13:40.686 --> 00:13:42.488
Wan Zhe's stall makes awesome shaved ice.

00:13:42.488 --> 00:13:44.089
Nothing on the menu is bad.

00:13:44.089 --> 00:13:46.125
But the taro balls take time.

00:13:46.125 --> 00:13:47.868
They cook them upon ordering.

00:13:51.230 --> 00:13:52.598
Drink up, it's a hot day.

00:13:52.598 --> 00:13:54.566
Scorching hot.

00:13:58.971 --> 00:14:00.806
Our food is here.

00:14:00.806 --> 00:14:02.527
That's too fast.

00:14:04.143 --> 00:14:06.737
Li Wan Zhe, what is this?

00:14:06.737 --> 00:14:08.136
Shaved ice.

00:14:09.515 --> 00:14:11.150
Li Wan Zhe.

00:14:11.150 --> 00:14:12.785
I think he's suffering from heat stroke.

00:14:12.785 --> 00:14:13.853
- Wan Zhe!
- What is this?

00:14:13.853 --> 00:14:16.222
- I'll give you a massage.
- Gosh, I'm sorry.

00:14:16.222 --> 00:14:17.223
- Sorry. I'll make another bowl for you.
- It's okay.

00:14:17.223 --> 00:14:18.490
-

00:14:18.490 --> 00:14:19.792
Hao Wei, help me with the customer.

00:14:19.792 --> 00:14:22.995
Sorry about that.

00:14:22.995 --> 00:14:24.987
Li Wan Zhe!

00:14:32.137 --> 00:14:35.574
One day, the shell came home.

00:14:35.574 --> 00:14:38.028
- It said...
- "I'm shelled."

00:14:43.549 --> 00:14:45.927
Do you know why vampires don't eat spicy food?

00:14:48.487 --> 00:14:50.900
Because they are like Blandimir.

00:14:53.325 --> 00:14:55.981
- Do you know...
- Just speak your mind.

00:15:01.300 --> 00:15:02.902
What does that card mean?

00:15:02.902 --> 00:15:05.571
What was all that about finding my way?

00:15:09.174 --> 00:15:13.679
Sometimes, cards are just prompts.

00:15:13.679 --> 00:15:15.647
They aren't answers.

00:15:19.285 --> 00:15:20.853
Here, take it.

00:15:22.522 --> 00:15:23.522
- Thanks.
- Not now.

00:15:23.522 --> 00:15:25.008
-

00:15:26.759 --> 00:15:28.989
- All right.
- Keep it.

00:15:31.363 --> 00:15:33.964
Oh, I was about to keep it.

00:16:02.761 --> 00:16:04.510
What?

00:16:04.510 --> 00:16:06.371
The massage?

00:16:10.035 --> 00:16:11.370
Ouch!

00:16:11.370 --> 00:16:13.038
So, you can feel pain?

00:16:13.038 --> 00:16:14.740
Duh.

00:16:14.740 --> 00:16:16.931
What is this new act now?

00:16:20.145 --> 00:16:21.647
An act for Xiao Hai?

00:16:21.647 --> 00:16:23.716
Don't say that name again.

00:16:23.716 --> 00:16:25.718
I just can't figure out why
he keeps confessing his love to me.

00:16:25.718 --> 00:16:27.519
Didn't you want to be in love?

00:16:27.519 --> 00:16:28.821
All that stuff about a passionate romance.

00:16:28.821 --> 00:16:29.822
Love has come knocking.
Why are you so shocked?

00:16:29.822 --> 00:16:30.956
-

00:16:30.956 --> 00:16:33.258
Just accept his love.

00:16:33.258 --> 00:16:36.395
I didn't know my wish would come true.

00:16:36.395 --> 00:16:38.630
Didn't you ask me to accept things?

00:16:39.531 --> 00:16:41.800
Fine, let's assume the wish came true.

00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:43.268
But I don't want to date Xiao Hai!

00:16:43.268 --> 00:16:45.471
We're like brothers, best buddies.

00:16:45.471 --> 00:16:46.505
We game together.
Now, you want us to be a couple?

00:16:46.505 --> 00:16:48.040
-

00:16:48.040 --> 00:16:49.141
Isn't that hella strange?
Well... It's impossible.

00:16:49.141 --> 00:16:51.876
-

00:16:53.946 --> 00:16:59.551
So, we have to find a way
to nullify the wishes.

00:17:33.685 --> 00:17:35.820
That's really rude.

00:17:45.164 --> 00:17:47.665
Nah, forget it.

00:17:50.569 --> 00:17:52.704
Hello. Good evening.

00:17:52.704 --> 00:17:55.448
Are you going to ask about He Xiang Yong?

00:17:56.942 --> 00:18:00.312
Xiang Yong went missing after a tiny mistake.

00:18:00.312 --> 00:18:01.780
Who knows where he's run off to?

00:18:01.780 --> 00:18:03.582
Has he called you?

00:18:03.582 --> 00:18:05.084
Nope.

00:18:05.084 --> 00:18:07.252
I'm here to find out where he is,

00:18:07.252 --> 00:18:09.888
and I'm not having it easy with him gone.

00:18:09.888 --> 00:18:11.890
He didn't contact you?

00:18:11.890 --> 00:18:13.292
Darn brat.

00:18:13.292 --> 00:18:14.915
Pick one.

00:18:22.968 --> 00:18:24.636
He might be in trouble.

00:18:24.636 --> 00:18:26.271
What trouble?

00:18:26.271 --> 00:18:29.441
Look for the answer yourself.

00:18:29.441 --> 00:18:30.809
Hang on, I chose that card.
Aren't you going to tell me what's on it?

00:18:30.809 --> 00:18:32.778
-

00:18:32.778 --> 00:18:34.413
What trouble will he be in?

00:18:34.413 --> 00:18:36.393
And who will he meet?

00:18:38.383 --> 00:18:40.449
I'm off to fulfill my mission.

00:18:41.787 --> 00:18:43.142
Miss!

00:18:46.024 --> 00:18:47.159
Miss!

00:18:47.159 --> 00:18:49.936
Finish your sentence!

00:19:08.225 --> 00:19:10.093
Li Wan Zhe!

00:19:12.797 --> 00:19:15.032
I have something to tell you!

00:19:16.955 --> 00:19:18.023
Come over here.

00:19:18.023 --> 00:19:20.092
I need to talk to you, too.

00:19:20.092 --> 00:19:21.492
Sit.

00:19:34.559 --> 00:19:36.059
- Actually...
- Actually...

00:19:40.632 --> 00:19:42.017
- I...
- I...

00:19:46.713 --> 00:19:48.019
- You...
- You...

00:19:49.121 --> 00:19:50.355
Forget it, you can go first.

00:19:50.355 --> 00:19:52.066
No, you go first.

00:19:55.127 --> 00:19:58.163
I don't know why I've suddenly
confessed your love.

00:19:58.163 --> 00:19:59.946
- But...
- Actually...

00:20:00.966 --> 00:20:04.002
This island has a strange myth.

00:20:04.002 --> 00:20:07.473
If shooting stars are streaking across the sky

00:20:07.473 --> 00:20:09.241
while you are doing something weird...

00:20:09.241 --> 00:20:10.442
Shooting stars?

00:20:10.442 --> 00:20:11.910
Yep, the shooting stars.

00:20:11.910 --> 00:20:13.279
The shooting stars are behind this.

00:20:13.279 --> 00:20:15.647
You don't really like me,
but you just ended up liking me.

00:20:15.647 --> 00:20:17.548
Yep, that's it.

00:20:18.484 --> 00:20:20.252
I'm really in love with you.

00:20:20.252 --> 00:20:22.494
I really think the shooting stars caused this.

00:20:23.489 --> 00:20:25.557
- Trust me.
- You trust me.

00:20:25.557 --> 00:20:27.025
Trust my trust in you.

00:20:27.025 --> 00:20:29.594
Trust your trust that's trusting...

00:20:32.598 --> 00:20:34.967
Just get a night's sleep.

00:20:34.967 --> 00:20:37.035
Tomorrow, everything will be back to normal.

00:20:37.035 --> 00:20:38.572
You...

00:20:38.572 --> 00:20:40.239
You've just been bewitched
by some strange power.

00:20:40.239 --> 00:20:42.741
So, you've been forced
to suddenly declare your love.

00:20:42.741 --> 00:20:44.176
Yes, that must be it.

00:20:44.176 --> 00:20:45.744
Yep.

00:20:45.744 --> 00:20:48.479
I like you, I mean it.

00:20:54.620 --> 00:20:56.688
You like me?

00:20:56.688 --> 00:20:59.102
Fine, what exactly do you like about me?

00:21:00.692 --> 00:21:02.094
I like your lovely eyes.
I like your tall nose.

00:21:02.094 --> 00:21:03.362
-

00:21:03.362 --> 00:21:04.530
I like your thick lips.
I like your long legs.

00:21:04.530 --> 00:21:05.631
-

00:21:05.631 --> 00:21:07.699
I like how filial you are.

00:21:07.699 --> 00:21:09.668
I like how you're an attentive friend.

00:21:09.668 --> 00:21:11.703
I like how you're so cheerful with everyone.

00:21:11.703 --> 00:21:14.306
I like the shaved ice you make for me

00:21:14.306 --> 00:21:17.576
with tons of extra plums.

00:21:17.576 --> 00:21:20.644
I like how you chomp down your food.

00:21:20.644 --> 00:21:22.681
I want to eat tons of good food with you.

00:21:22.681 --> 00:21:24.583
Okay.

00:21:24.583 --> 00:21:26.485
All right, I got it.

00:21:26.485 --> 00:21:29.288
How are you going to prove your words?

00:21:29.288 --> 00:21:31.656
How do you want me to prove them?

00:21:34.326 --> 00:21:35.827
Got it.

00:21:35.827 --> 00:21:37.595
Turtle egg cakes.

00:21:39.170 --> 00:21:41.738
I'll buy them for you tomorrow morning.

00:21:42.601 --> 00:21:43.988
Wait.

00:21:44.902 --> 00:21:47.935
Turtle egg cakes? You'll get them?

00:21:52.544 --> 00:21:56.582
But I'm craving pork knuckle rice.

00:21:56.582 --> 00:21:59.056
The one sold at Siping Street, New Taipei.

00:21:59.985 --> 00:22:01.610
How do you know?

00:22:03.488 --> 00:22:04.890
Hang on.

00:22:04.890 --> 00:22:06.627
There's more.

00:22:07.960 --> 00:22:10.195
I also want to have the charcoal toast sandwich
from Yancheng District, Kaohsiung,

00:22:10.195 --> 00:22:11.697
squid vermicelli from Guohua Street, Tainan,

00:22:11.697 --> 00:22:13.131
vinegar cold noodles
from Wenhua Street, Chiayi,

00:22:13.131 --> 00:22:14.800
Heizhuyuan chicken feet,
stinky tofu from Heping Street,

00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:15.901
jute leaves soup from Taichung's second market,

00:22:15.901 --> 00:22:16.900
rolled wraps from Hsinchu's City God Temple,

00:22:16.900 --> 00:22:18.803
and garlic meat soup
from Taishan Road, Yilan.

00:22:20.339 --> 00:22:22.889
How's that? Can't buy them all, huh?

00:22:29.815 --> 00:22:31.487
Let me think about it.

00:22:39.224 --> 00:22:40.325
When you've bought them all,
we can discuss your feelings for me.

00:22:40.325 --> 00:22:42.560
-

00:22:50.502 --> 00:22:53.138
He probably can't buy them all.

00:22:53.138 --> 00:22:55.291
Yeah, it's impossible.

00:22:56.208 --> 00:22:57.709
No way he can do it.

00:22:57.709 --> 00:22:59.985
Impossible.

00:23:01.380 --> 00:23:03.907
Jiao has been acting weird lately.

00:23:04.816 --> 00:23:06.084
He keeps coming for consultations.
He's totally fine, though.

00:23:06.084 --> 00:23:08.373
-

00:23:09.755 --> 00:23:13.685
But he comes just to ask about you.

00:23:17.362 --> 00:23:19.197
What's up?

00:23:19.197 --> 00:23:20.798
Bad mood?

00:23:23.902 --> 00:23:26.336
It's my son.

00:23:26.336 --> 00:23:27.605
Who knows what trouble he's stirred.

00:23:27.605 --> 00:23:29.508
He's quit his job and come back here.

00:23:29.508 --> 00:23:32.711
And now, he's recruited some...

00:23:32.711 --> 00:23:36.315
university classmate to work at our inn.

00:23:36.315 --> 00:23:38.406
I can't figure him out.

00:23:38.406 --> 00:23:41.620
It is rather strange.

00:23:41.620 --> 00:23:43.955
What's going on?

00:23:43.955 --> 00:23:46.611
How about you ask the publishing house?

00:23:49.661 --> 00:23:52.953
He's a grown man.
Can't he handle his own problems?

00:23:54.799 --> 00:23:56.067
True...

00:23:56.067 --> 00:23:58.099
I bet he's being stubborn.

00:24:01.673 --> 00:24:03.475
When Xiang Yong was young,
he had a high fever.

00:24:03.475 --> 00:24:05.343
-

00:24:05.343 --> 00:24:07.546
You carried him across half the island to me.

00:24:07.546 --> 00:24:11.249
Never even thought to bike over.

00:24:11.249 --> 00:24:13.519
Do you know what you said to me?

00:24:13.519 --> 00:24:14.953
What did I say?

00:24:14.953 --> 00:24:19.858
You said parents are tasked
with a lifetime of worrying.

00:24:19.858 --> 00:24:22.694
No matter how old their children are,

00:24:22.694 --> 00:24:26.565
parents never stop worrying.

00:24:26.565 --> 00:24:28.051
Right?

00:24:34.306 --> 00:24:39.544
Why do these words
sound so gross coming from you?

00:24:39.544 --> 00:24:41.579
That better be true.

00:24:43.548 --> 00:24:45.417
Forget it.

00:24:45.417 --> 00:24:47.319
He's a grown man now.

00:24:47.319 --> 00:24:50.922
I should be living a peaceful life now.

00:24:50.922 --> 00:24:53.408
But worry is written all over your face.

00:24:54.860 --> 00:24:57.963
Don't waste your time chatting
and drinking with me.

00:24:57.963 --> 00:25:00.265
How about trying to
get to the bottom of things?

00:25:00.265 --> 00:25:03.171
You need to know where to start
when resolving problems.

00:25:06.671 --> 00:25:09.007
You're just all talk.

00:25:09.007 --> 00:25:12.009
When are you going to finish that origami boat?

00:25:16.014 --> 00:25:17.349
- I can burn it for you in the afterlife.
- Screw off.

00:25:17.349 --> 00:25:20.014
-

00:25:46.244 --> 00:25:49.848
Face the sea and count...

00:25:49.848 --> 00:25:52.284
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:25:52.284 --> 00:25:54.119
Wan Zhe's stall makes awesome shaved ice.

00:25:54.119 --> 00:25:55.620
Nothing on the menu is bad.

00:25:55.620 --> 00:25:57.622
But the taro balls take time.

00:25:57.622 --> 00:25:59.566
They cook them upon ordering.

00:26:10.502 --> 00:26:12.405
What's wrong?

00:26:15.407 --> 00:26:17.441
Don't hurl your tower!

00:26:51.571 --> 00:26:53.840
[Home is He-re?]

00:27:00.018 --> 00:27:01.019
Zhong Xiao You. Something's not right.

00:27:01.019 --> 00:27:02.387
-

00:27:02.387 --> 00:27:04.221
What's up?

00:27:05.256 --> 00:27:07.325
When I brought breakfast to Xi Xi,

00:27:07.325 --> 00:27:09.361
she refused to leave her room.

00:27:09.361 --> 00:27:10.729
I also heard some strange noises.
Stuff like this...

00:27:10.729 --> 00:27:12.681
-

00:27:14.265 --> 00:27:16.468
After that, some crashing sounds.

00:27:16.468 --> 00:27:19.104
Did someone visit her?

00:27:19.104 --> 00:27:20.955
She's probably fine.

00:27:21.940 --> 00:27:23.808
That's just how comic artists are.

00:27:23.808 --> 00:27:25.543
I'm sure she's being rushed to meet deadlines.

00:27:25.543 --> 00:27:27.779
So, she's locked herself in
and unleashed her alter ego.

00:27:27.779 --> 00:27:30.248
But she can't imprison herself like this.

00:27:30.248 --> 00:27:31.316
What if she's in trouble?
How do we help her?

00:27:31.316 --> 00:27:32.651
-

00:27:32.651 --> 00:27:34.494
She'll be fine.

00:27:39.891 --> 00:27:41.693
Excuse me.

00:27:41.693 --> 00:27:43.695
I'll call Mr. He.

00:27:43.695 --> 00:27:45.543
Chen Hao Wei.

00:27:47.098 --> 00:27:48.491
What?

00:27:49.700 --> 00:27:51.903
How about you go buy some stuff?

00:27:51.903 --> 00:27:53.405
What stuff?

00:27:53.405 --> 00:27:55.459
Bitter gourd and black tea.

00:27:57.542 --> 00:27:59.482
Why do I have to buy them?

00:28:01.179 --> 00:28:02.247
Fine. You can call Mr. He.

00:28:02.247 --> 00:28:03.481
-

00:28:03.481 --> 00:28:06.885
When he's back, the room
should be completely demolished.

00:28:06.885 --> 00:28:08.886
It's your fault if shit goes down.

00:28:10.889 --> 00:28:14.292
Do you need sugar in your green tea?

00:28:14.292 --> 00:28:16.194
Black tea, no sugar.

00:28:16.194 --> 00:28:18.155
Black tea, no sugar.

00:28:22.167 --> 00:28:23.268
But do I get white or green bitter gourd?

00:28:23.268 --> 00:28:25.103
Whichever.

00:28:25.103 --> 00:28:26.875
Hurry up.

00:28:29.446 --> 00:28:30.994
I don't get it.

00:28:38.925 --> 00:28:40.933
[Home is He-re]

00:28:45.023 --> 00:28:47.112
He's taking so long.

00:29:10.615 --> 00:29:12.283
Hey, this is Home is He-re.

00:29:12.283 --> 00:29:13.317
Xiao You. I'll leave the island for a bit.

00:29:13.317 --> 00:29:14.419
-

00:29:14.419 --> 00:29:16.755
A bunch of fishing tour groups might visit.

00:29:16.755 --> 00:29:17.822
Make sure five rooms are available.
Don't accept too many guests.

00:29:17.822 --> 00:29:19.457
-

00:29:19.457 --> 00:29:20.525
- Call me if there are issues.
- When will you be back?

00:29:20.525 --> 00:29:22.895
-

00:29:22.895 --> 00:29:24.596
Hello?

00:29:24.596 --> 00:29:26.048
Hey!

00:29:29.434 --> 00:29:31.002
He knows there are tour groups,

00:29:31.002 --> 00:29:33.616
but he's leaving the inn to two part-timers.

00:29:47.118 --> 00:29:48.588
I'm back.

00:29:50.855 --> 00:29:52.023
You got the right stuff, yeah?
Black tea?

00:29:52.023 --> 00:29:53.224
-

00:29:53.224 --> 00:29:55.027
Yep, black tea.

00:29:55.027 --> 00:29:57.086
But I bought both types of bitter gourd.

00:29:57.086 --> 00:29:58.075
[Mr. He: 6/26 Fishing Tour Group]
[Inn full booking, no other guests]

00:29:58.075 --> 00:30:00.744
It's fine. I just need bitter gourd.

00:30:15.346 --> 00:30:16.715
I made some tea for you.
It's by the door.

00:30:16.715 --> 00:30:18.578
-

00:30:42.874 --> 00:30:44.142
What?

00:30:44.142 --> 00:30:46.035
Need to destress too?

00:30:47.512 --> 00:30:49.080
Nah.

00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:51.315
I just want to know if it's effective.

00:30:56.154 --> 00:30:58.650
Never heard of "bitter before the sweet"?

00:31:01.459 --> 00:31:05.363
The brain has four chemicals
that trigger happiness:

00:31:05.363 --> 00:31:08.933
Serotonin, Dopamine, Endorphins, and Oxytocin.

00:31:08.933 --> 00:31:11.536
The bitterness in bitter gourds
triggers endorphins in the brain,

00:31:11.536 --> 00:31:14.572
while black tea is packed with
tea polyphenols and antioxidants.

00:31:14.572 --> 00:31:16.608
So, bitter gourd with black tea can help one destress.

00:31:16.608 --> 00:31:18.941
-

00:31:19.777 --> 00:31:20.912
- Is that really true?
- Of course.

00:31:20.912 --> 00:31:21.946
-

00:31:21.946 --> 00:31:23.878
I read it somewhere.

00:31:26.084 --> 00:31:28.920
You read such books?

00:31:28.920 --> 00:31:30.655
Yeah.

00:31:30.655 --> 00:31:32.056
I don't have many friends.
When I have time, I read.

00:31:32.056 --> 00:31:34.029
-

00:31:37.962 --> 00:31:41.232
You talk so slowly,
but you're pretty reliable now.

00:31:41.232 --> 00:31:44.034
-

00:31:47.272 --> 00:31:49.206
You didn't lie to me today.

00:31:51.976 --> 00:31:53.933
Do I lie to you often?

00:31:54.879 --> 00:31:59.265
I've only said one real lie to you.

00:32:00.718 --> 00:32:02.219
What was it?

00:32:06.524 --> 00:32:11.089
He said you're the last person
he wants to remember.

00:32:16.968 --> 00:32:18.403
On the first night.

00:32:18.403 --> 00:32:20.438
The stuff I told you on the rooftop.

00:32:20.438 --> 00:32:22.373
Night time...

00:32:22.373 --> 00:32:24.141
Which was it?

00:32:24.909 --> 00:32:27.074
Doesn't matter if you've already forgotten.

00:32:34.652 --> 00:32:36.253
How about this?

00:32:36.921 --> 00:32:39.257
Let's play a game.

00:32:39.257 --> 00:32:40.959
We'll ask each other questions.

00:32:40.959 --> 00:32:42.927
But we have to be honest.

00:32:42.927 --> 00:32:44.437
Up for it?

00:32:47.165 --> 00:32:48.628
Ask away.

00:32:58.543 --> 00:33:01.317
Did I make He Xiang Yong leave?

00:33:09.087 --> 00:33:10.754
Nah.

00:33:12.423 --> 00:33:13.991
Are you serious?

00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:16.072
Yep.

00:33:22.033 --> 00:33:23.659
Your turn.

00:33:41.119 --> 00:33:43.020
What are you doing?

00:33:47.158 --> 00:33:49.655
Did you date He Xiang Yong?

00:33:52.263 --> 00:33:55.724
Why have you come to Starry Islet
to look for him?

00:34:07.945 --> 00:34:10.081
What is Chen Hao Wei up to?
[Epilogue]

00:34:10.081 --> 00:34:12.216
Can he stop doing everything alone?

00:34:12.216 --> 00:34:14.519
Does he think he's Kobe Bryant?

00:34:14.519 --> 00:34:15.853
Soloing every single thing.

00:34:15.853 --> 00:34:17.789
- About today...
- Sorry.

00:34:17.789 --> 00:34:19.457
Basketball is a team sport, all right?

00:34:19.457 --> 00:34:20.658
You want to make a shot,
but you can't even score.

00:34:20.658 --> 00:34:21.759
-

00:34:21.759 --> 00:34:23.060
What the hell?

00:34:24.228 --> 00:34:26.069
I don't want to be on his team anymore.

00:34:50.021 --> 00:34:51.622
Why are you here?

00:34:51.622 --> 00:34:53.157
I'm fine.

00:34:53.157 --> 00:34:55.166
It's just a competition.

00:34:58.463 --> 00:34:59.497
He Xiang Yong.

00:34:59.497 --> 00:35:02.467
Now, others won't see you that you're upset.

00:35:02.467 --> 00:35:03.501
- Do you know why I've come looking for you?
- I'm not upset.

00:35:03.501 --> 00:35:05.169
-

00:35:05.169 --> 00:35:07.171
I'm fine.

00:35:07.171 --> 00:35:09.240
Just laugh when you want to.

00:35:09.240 --> 00:35:12.043
Cry when you want to.

00:35:12.043 --> 00:35:14.178
Don't care what others think about you.

00:35:14.178 --> 00:35:16.146
Because when I find you,

00:35:16.940 --> 00:35:19.700
I feel like I can find myself.

00:35:52.583 --> 00:35:53.814
He.

00:35:54.934 --> 00:35:56.787
Sorry for interrupting.

00:35:56.787 --> 00:35:59.023
You're He Xiang Yong, aren't you?

00:35:59.023 --> 00:36:02.494
This isn't a fight, it's a tiff.

00:36:02.494 --> 00:36:03.526
I want to see him because I want to beat him up.

00:36:03.526 --> 00:36:04.728
-

00:36:04.728 --> 00:36:07.265
Surprise.

00:36:07.265 --> 00:36:10.000
Xiang Yong, your favorite watermelon candy.